Summary: Email is down

Fax machine low on toner

Resolution: Inspected the laptop and found that the battery was not fully plugged in.  After snapping it in firmly, it booted.

Summary: Customer reports losing network connectivity
Resolution: Visited the users desk and found the network cable connector was faulty.  Replaced the patch cable and discarded the broken one.

Summary: User having trouble with Firefox browser
Resolution:
Ttemporarily disabling IMAP SSL will can help:

      Disable SSL in Netscape 7.x or Mozilla:

      Ensure that you are in your e-mail client and select Mail and Newsgroups Account Settings under the Edit menu.
      Click on Server Settings under your Princeton IMAP account.
      Uncheck the box for Use Secure Connection (SSL). open Netscape, click on the Edit menu and select Preferences. In the Preferences window, double-click on Mail & Newsgroups and select Mail Servers from the list that drops down. Highlight imap.Princeton.edu and click the Edit button.
      Click on the IMAP tab and uncheck the box for Use Secure Connection (SSL).
      Click OK and try loading your Inbox again by clicking on the Get Msgs icon. If this does not load your Inbox, proceed with the additional troubleshooting steps below.
